          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1678879532721-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the onion is softening, dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 500ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[650ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[900ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong>, <strong>browned chicken</strong>, <strong>thyme</strong> (chuck it in, stalks and all!) and 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> flour </strong>to the pan</p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
